Issue: Error in execution of CLM_EXPORT file as file for 31st Jan 18 is not received from ICW Business Impact: Delay in file execution is critical to Iberia cards since it holds data of the active customers in Spain based on which business rules are created to calculate the accrued points, programs etc. Analysis: File arrived late due to which the sequence of the files have changed due to which IBCARDS was not able to identify the files with respect to the date and sequence number generated..Therefore manually re ran the member files. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Member's file to successfully process the file. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

column7: Revisar si las pasarelas de los mercados de Brasil y Reino Unido no presentan ningún problema
column13: 2/8/2018 9:19:11 PM, NIIT.prani, Issue Description : Check if the gateways of the markets of Brazil and the United Kingdom do not present any problem Business impact : No impact as all the ERRORS occurred are the genuine ones. Action taken: We have seen the trend for all the listed markets and found a slight increment in KO transactions for FR, IT and GB markets on 31st in comparison of 30th Jan’18 and reason could be the slight hike in total bookings. Also we have observed that all the ERRORS occurred are the genuine ones. No abnormality seen during this period. As we do not see any issues with these markets, we are closing this incident. There was communication going on with the user. Please find the attached mail for all the relevant information. 2/2/2018 6:34:25 PM, NIIT.prani, We have sent the below update to contact user. For more info, Please see the attached mail. "We have seen the trend for all the listed markets and found a slight increment in KO transactions for FR, IT and GB markets on 31st in comparison of 30th Jan’18 and reason could be the slight hike in total bookings. Also we have observed that all the ERRORS occurred are the genuine ones. No abnormality seen during this period. As we do not see any issues with these markets, Please confirm if we are good to close this incident. Below are few genuine ERRORS: Error_al_comprobar_el_resultado_de_autenticación_de_la_operación_en_curso Fondos Insuficientes CC_DENIED Respuesta_rechazado_de_CyberSource" 2/1/2018 11:48:39 PM, NIIT.rjha, We have been investigating the KO transactions for few markets from the below list and found that all the ERRORS occurred at different time-stamps caused by several reasons in which most of the reasons are genuine ones. We are investigating it further and also checking the trend for all the mentioned markets. We sent mail to Raul requesting downgrading the priority. Downgrading priority to medium after getting confirmation. We are further investigating. Mail attached. 2/1/2018 11:48:23 PM, NIIT.abansal, relevant stakeholders have been advised this is not issue anymore reducing priority as per attached email 2/1/2018 7:42:37 PM, NIIT.rjha, We checked current trend and it seems payment is working fine for given markets. Resolution: We have raised the issue with ATOS and asked them to reactivate the FF57589368. we later on, got confirmation from Atos that they have activated the FF57589368. Problem Ticket Required: NO, this issue was raised because the FF57589368 has been cancelled, by mistake & is one of an instance. Can this incident be prevented: No, This is is one of an instance and cases like these are handle by third party so no preventive action can be taken from our end.

column13: Issue: Consulta sobre importes de ficheros ancilleries de I2 Impact: Bajo Root Causes: Si analizamos por ejemplo al billete 4010731076 que se envió ayer: 060;01;4010731076; ; ;M9LPCC1A ;31/01/2018;7849447; ; ;00000003000;EUR2;00000003000;CCCA1000 ;00000003000 060;02;4010731076; ; ;M9LPCC1A ;31/01/2018;7849447; ; ;00000000000;EUR2;00000000000;CCCA1000 ;00000003000 Estos importes que marcamos en color se corresponden con el importe de la forma de pago a nivel contrato, en el cupón 1 viene la primera forma de pago, en el 2 viene la 2ª... así es cómo está diseñado este proceso, por eso veis que al final todo el importe lo tiene el cupón 1. Este proceso parte directamente de los ficheros en formato BSP, es antes del prorrateo a nivel cupón, no se dispone de ese valor para enviar. En la parte de IB el funcionamiento que está implementado tira directamente de Base de datos, dónde ya se tiene el prorrateo a nivel cupón, y por ello la información que se obtiene es distinta y si va el dato prorrateado. Steps taken: Se informa al cliente.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

Problem Ticket Required: No, This is a alarm Incident which arrives when the system starts facing issues(it requires manual check), but the code handles the connections after some time duration.We need to check the health of the system through designated logs. column13: Issue: ELK ibclogec1.ib client node was having high swap area occupied Business Impact: Kibana search can get impacted as the client nodes handle request and response from kibana. Analysis: Elasticsearch services were down on client node as a result of high swap memory area occupied. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node and it joined the cluster back. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No). No, as client nodes have light memory leak thus after running for some time, they start occupying swap memory. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) : No, in elastic search client nodes have light memory leak as the background is build in Java, we can not prevent client nodes from consuming large swap memory after running for long time.

Root Cause: En la rutina I32RMIL2 accede a la tabla BEACU.TACUFMI con la cia del acuerdo y la clase equivalente para recuperar el factor millas clase. El proceso falla porque no existe el factor millas clase. Steps Taken: Solicitud para modificar la fecha FMIFINI para la cia y la clase agrupada de la tabla BEACU.TACUFMI. Recibido el aviso que se modifico la fecha FMIFINI, relanzar el proceso desde el paso fallado. Termina OK.

column7: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 94.32%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column13: Issue: ELK - high swap area was occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib. Analysis: After running for some time client nodes consume swap memory. Thus it is required to restart the elasticsearch services. Business Impact: Users will not be able to make request and response from Kibana if client node leaves the cluster. Hence it is important that both the client nodes in cluster are up and running. Resolution: we restarted the elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib and it is up and running now. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to start services on client nodes. Can this incident be prevented: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to restart elasticservices on client nodes

Issue: ELK - high swap area was occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib. Analysis: After running for some time client nodes consume swap memory. Thus it is required to restart the elasticsearch services. Business Impact: Users will not be able to make request and response from Kibana if client node leaves the cluster. Hence it is important that both the client nodes in cluster are up and running. Resolution: we restarted the elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib and it is up and running now. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to start services on client nodes. Can this incident be prevented: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to restart elasticservices on client nodes

column7: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 98.84%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column13: Issue: ELK - high swap area was occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib. Analysis: After running for some time client nodes consume swap memory. Thus it is required to restart the elasticsearch services. Business Impact: Users will not be able to make request and response from Kibana if client node leaves the cluster. Hence it is important that both the client nodes in cluster are up and running. Resolution: we restarted the elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib and it is up and running now. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to start services on client nodes. Can this incident be prevented: No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from sometime. Thus it is important to restart elasticservices on client nodes

ISSUE: Did not received the Monthly Point Balance file. IMAPCT: This file has information monthly billing points based on which Rewards of the customer is calculated. ANALYSIS: The system did not receive the IB_MONTHLY_POINTS_BALANCE_20180203.csv file which resulted in KO. RESOLUTION: Asked the ICW Team to re-send the file on the FTP server again and once the file was received, manually re-ran load plan. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. As the ICW Team had connection issues between IB and BA ports therefor you are not able to receive  IB_MONTHLY_POINTS_BALANCE* file . CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The process will fail if the process do not receive the file on time.
Resuelto

column13: Issue: Unable to login to the Hyperion GaudiPR4 platform. Impact The server was down because of which users were not able to login to the platform Later the scheduled reports also did failed to execute. Analysis: The virtual machine for GaudiPR4 was down,was not able to login to the RDC.when multiple reports were executing or multiple user logged in at the same time and the CPU performance reached 98-100% the services went down. Actions Taken: Opened a incident to Windows ES for Restarting the virtual machine for GAUDIPR4. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The services were restarted and therefore , no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The services were restarted and therefore , no issue with the application.

column13: Issue: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors. Impact: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis: As per the process we checked the database for errors/blocking session, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned dao logs for the specified errors. Resolution: Since the errors stopped appearing in the log and there were no blocking session in DB, so we are closing this INC. Problem Ticket Required: No, This is a alarm Incident which arrives when the system starts facing issues(it requires manual check), but the code handles the connections after some time duration.We need to check the health of the system through designated logs. Can this incident be prevented: No

column13: Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec2.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec2.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

Issue: In Semi-automatic notifications" that are dated Feb 5th , although user have "Rejected" them every day, they go out again. Impact: User was getting email alerts again and again for semi-automatic notification for same rejected flight. Analysis: As per analysis in lower environment there are many tables are impacted (dependant) by rejecting flight list. As per business logic user has to choose the reject cause option from the menu(Avisado Manualmente). After that related data will be update and delete from the tables e.g. ibc_notifications,ibc_semiaut_notif_pending,IBC_GROUPS_TAB,ibc_failed_notifications. Resolution: Found that the status in ibc_semiaut_notif_pending not been updated. We have updated the states than the flight stops reappearing. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED:NO: We will wait for this issue to replicate again in production, if this happens again then we will raise a problem ticket. CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED:NO:Its an intermittent issue. When user has rejected the flight thtough the portal may be few tables not get updated in db.

column13: Análisis de impacto: No aplica Acciones realizadas: Simulamos la generación del informe con los filtros expuestos por la usuaria y generamos el infomre correctamente.Llamamos a la usuaria y no está. Hablamos con una compañera (APMIB.Méndez Alonso, Cecilia Patricia <APMIB.cpmendez@iberia.es>) y concluimos que el problema es de la configuración de memoria del pc del usuario que no soporta la generación del inofmre. Nos indica la usuaria que podemos cerrar la incidencia ya que comprobamos con ella que su pc es de 32 bits y no admite más de 1GB de memoria para AMOS. Nos indica que ya se encarga ella de hablar con su compalera y que la opción que le aconsejo de actualizar a 64 bits no lo ve claro ya que son de empresa externa a iberia, que mejor partirán los datos filtrando para que el volumen de memoria consumida sea menor Pruebas realizadas: No aplica

column13: Issue : User unable to logout of Genesys control unit. Needs a forceful logout. Impact : User unable to logout & hence unable to work. Analysis : Since the support of such instances is provided by the BT team, we have asked them to open an Incident at their end. Steps Taken to Resolve : Since the support of such instances is provided by the BT team, we have asked them to open an Incident at their end. column7: **REOPENED**[CIP] OB20243932 T9 fare has accrued points
column13: Issue: OB20243932 T9 fare has accrued points Impact: Only account OB20243932 Analysis: It has come to our knowledge that this issue is part of a major pending farebasis development on IBERIA. In this case, farebasis arrived to Cobol systems as VDNNNB/T9. As you know, T9 is the farebasis for discounted ticket. However, this system is not prepared to receive the slash (/), hence it automatically considered only the first part of the farebasis (VDNNNB) and assigned the code ‘00’ (eligible to accrue). Therefore, the ticket passed on to Comarch like that, with 00 code, and hence it accrue points. Resolution: We have already discussed this with the Business team (Ana de la Llave) and she has confirmed that no action should be made on the ticket. That is, the points that were incorrectly posted, are not to be withdrawn.

column7: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 100.00%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGro
column13: Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.
Procedemos al reinicio de la contraseña del usuario tras seguir el proceso de seguridad.

FE Name: Zain Hussain Date of intervention: 07/02/2018 & 16/02/2018 On site hours: 03:00 07/02/2018 Off site hours: NA Work done: The engineer has been onsite 07/02/2018 from 1:00 p.m. to 3:00 p.m. with a travel time of 30 minutes. The engineer has reviewed the equipment and executed a diagnosis of RAM and hard disk. In the verification tests a hard disk failure is obtained and a replacement of the hard disk drive is requested. The user has said that they need that position to work for what a supervisor has authorized to move a team close to the position so that the user continues working. The CPU PMIKQ02 is replaced by the CPU PMIKQ08 so that the user can continue working. The spare PC sent by Mulesol has been delivered to the Engineer. Today 16/02/2018 the engineer has spoken with the user of this incident but this time he has spoken with the head of Iberia CUP, and has commented that having replaced the equipment damaged by a team that did not use the incidence is resolved for them. Therefore, it is not necessary to install another spare equipment and do not want it since it will not be useful. The head of Iberia CUP was not in the conversation the other day, so it could have hurt the decision and does not want the team. We will bring the Spare back to Mulesol Workshop MAD Iberia User: Mati, Iberia CUP. Release Name: Mati, Iberia CUP.

column7: Alert received: INFORMACION ADICIONAL: ( ibcdwl5 ) Se ha encontrado el error BOOKING_FATAL \( Er
column13: 2/7/2018 6:37:42 PM, NIIT.prani, Issue Description: Error BOOKING_FATAL \ (Error in Booking Flow Manager \) has been found 182 times in the last check in the file /wl_app/ibcom_A/apli/logs/booking.out Business impact: There is no impact on bookings as ERRORS occurred temporarily. Action taken: We have investigated and found that Error "Error en Gestor del Flujo de Reservas" received many times around 11:15 AM Madrid time due to " Error no controlado (Could not get JDBC Connection; nested exception is weblogic.jdbc.extensions.PoolDisabledSQLException: weblogic.common.resourcepool.ResourceDisabledException: Pool Ibcom ibcompre_delivery bdracl iagcom is Suspended, cannot allocate resources to applications..). This might be due to a temporary glitch at weblogic side as database team confirmed earlier that this ERROR belongs to weblogic. ERROR has stopped now. Last ERROR occurred at 11:33 AM madrid time. We have monitored it for a while and found that no more ERRORS occured since then. Hence, we are resolving this incident now.

column7: LINUX_sun - ibclogec1.ib : Swap area occupied 92.55%. Assign incidence SERVICIOS_CKI_GAR SupportGrou
column13: Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

Cash & Avios authorizations are made from IB.com and / or from .NET. So that, whoever does it, the TKT can be issued later, ATOS informs us through a message of the creation of the authorization. We (RES) register the F5 authorization and you (TKT) call us to validate it. But, for a long time, we have enough errors (XTCAs) in the processing of these messages. These errors occur because in the message, in the field dedicated to the CASH part, comes a number with negatives. This is the message received for the authorization that you comment IFIA 0FF12634515 / LGTUIW00 / 000000033000FFP18499444 / IB3232 S20180213MADFCO0000000000000000000000083600 / IB3237 O20180214FCOMAD0000000000000000000000083600 / 2CAV / / 0 / EUR / 0 / 0000-18458 / 0 In yellow, the wrong data. In his day I tried to get someone to take action on the matter, but I did not succeed.” Mail Attached.

column7: LHRSBC - HFM CARGO IB - unable to retrieve
column13: Hi Richard, Fortunately we have found the cause which not let you to retrieve the template values. In the template, the column B14 retrieve the smartview connection name (HFMPROD_IAGCHFM), in this case, the connection name of the user who create the template, and your connection name for HFM prod is “HFM” (see the private connections panel). To correct this, you need to change your connection name. Second click on your connection and select “change name” to change it from ‘HFM’ to ‘HFMPROD_IAGCHFM’. Then refresh the template and you should see the correct values. Thanks and regards HFM Support Alternative contact point for any escalations: cmaroto@iberia.es or mbaranda@everis.com

column13: Issue: Failure in load processing of CLM_Export file for 11th Feb 2018. Analysis: We found that there was a delay from ICW in sending the daily CLM file on 12th Feb 2018. Business Impact: Delay in file execution is critical to Iberia cards since it holds data of the active customers in Spain based on which business rules are created to calculate the accrued points, programs etc. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for CLM_export file to successfully process the file. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) No, as the file arrived late from the source team due to some technical errors at their end which caused the ODI plan to fail. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) Yes, source team should send the required files on time in order to prevent such incidents.

column7: Fallo en proceso semanal de infare
column13: Issue: we got an Error in process of obtaining the weekly file of infare Impact:If This PROCESS fails, user will not receive file. analysis: The infare weekly process only executes on Monday and it depends on the daily infare file that we download from INFARE server. This process begins at 9:00 and we got the file at 9:06 so for that reason the process failed resolution: We have re run the the below process sh /IBairprice/INFARE/infare_W/bin/sh/carga_IW.sh & and and got the Ok Email indicating that daily file of infare has successfully ran. Problem ticket required: NO, this is due to late arrival of the file.. Can this issue be prevented: NO, this is due to late arrival of the file.

column13: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO, because its a pseudo Alarm and we have already worked with Database team to extend the pool size. <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the databse connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had already asked DBS to increase the Pool size.

column7: Open incidence - Error in the IB-WEEKLY-MFLS-20180211090005.dat file
column13: Issue:-BI team has received the value of KMS 0 in IB-WEEKLY-MFLS-20180211090005.dat file. Impact:- BI Team was unable to load this file into database of British Airways. Analysis:-We did back tracking and investigate, there is PLSQL procedure CARGA_CIUDADES_DISTANCIA which has not run before generating this file and master tables was not updated. Resolution:-We Rerun the CARGA_CIUDADES_DISTANCIA procedure with the date of Sunday after the completion of this procedure,regenerate the file and send it to the BI team. Problem ticket required: No, The problem is known, CARGA_CIUDADES_DISTANCIA procedure should be schedule in the same script and should be execute before generating the file. Can this issue is prevented: Yes, Normal change is required to prevent this issue in future.

Issue: For 18 minutes we can not access the iberia plus application. This incidence is affecting the 3 platform (Bogota, Seville and Lisbon) Impact: user will not able to perform IBPLUS transactions. Analysis:we have checked with ATOS and and find Resolution: we have raised Issue with ATOS and find that that there are users who have open the application up to 3 times and this is not operational because each session automatically closes when they have been using it for 1 hour without giving that error, in addition to saturating the connections to BBDD. we have asked the users Please try not to open new connections of the application unless it is strictly necessary, or if you are not using it frequently, close it when you finish the steps that you are doing. Although, we have already got confirmation from users that now they able to access application. Problem Ticket: No, as these issue occurs when multiple users face issue accessing the application, which leads to saturation of Database Preventive measures: No, It is solely based on Agents how they use the application.

the planned order will be converted to purchase requisitons when the requirement date is reached. There is a difference in the way MD01(MRP job) and MD03 (Single material planning) is run. MD03 screen values (like Modo planificación, Crear lista MRP, Crear solicitud de pedido etc..) will have priority over other configuration and variables in the system while in MD01, screen values are only considered as default values (i.e other system wide settings will be considered which should be the case). Thats why when you are MD03 and selecting the option 1 for Crear solicitud de pedido, the system is creating purchase requisition for future forecasted requirements now itself. Hope it clarifies your doubt. Let us know if you need more help. Thank you.

column13: Se llama a la usuaria para confirmar si podemos cerrar la incidencia ya que el problema se debia a la caida de sistemas de ayer 13 de febrero.

dia 13, se analiza la ase de datos para detectar posibles bloqueos, no apaprece ninguan sesion bloqueada. Se analiza el entorno rvisando todas las maquinas por si hubiera algun proceso que realentice la aplicaion, pero no se encuentra nada. Se accede a la aplicacion y se navega por ella por distintas opciones utilizadas frecuentemente por los equipos de reclamaciones sion detectar ningun problema. Se solicta mas informacion al respecto para tratar de detectar el error. dia 14, se informa por parte de los agentes que la incidencia se estuvo produciendo el dia 13 durante unas dos horas y que en esos momentos la aplicacion funcionaba con normalidad. Se analiza la plataforma y no se detecta nada anomalo. Dia 15, se analiza la plataforma a la misma hora que se reporto la incidencia por parte de los usuarios y no se detecta nada. Todos los procesos de los que es propietario el usuario administrador de siebel estan controlados pero existen en la plataforma otros procesos no controlados por Mantenimiento CRM y que podrian ser los causantes de un problema puntual de rendimiento Cerramos la incidencia.
Se comprueba acceso tras desbloqueo.
[BT] se informa al cliente que sin la contraseña no se puede reconfigurar la IPAD, y ademas no se trata de una INC si no de una Peticion. cerramos la INC

Later he was successfully able to get the BC. We know as per the procedure, if the AQQ or ESTA is not OK, the host must re-send the information to the American TSA to answer if it allows the passenger to be billed or not. Can you Please check if the mentioned request was made or something missing from your end- so that we can communicate further to business. If everything OK, can you please provide some instances on that. Attached Screen. ================================== Hola equipo, Vemos en los registros que el PAX había cargado todos los documentos requeridos cuando recibió el mensaje de error AQQ_SELECTEE . Más tarde logró con éxito el BC. Sabemos que según el procedimiento, si AQQ o ESTA no están OK, el host debe volver a enviar la información a la TSA estadounidense para que responda si permite facturar al pasajero o no. ¿Puede verificar si se realizó la solicitud mencionada o falta algo de su lado, para que podamos comunicarnos más con el negocio? column7: Queue 22 - No se ha encontrado el RM con los datos del robot.
column13: 2/23/2018 8:04:37 PM, NIIT.averma, Hi Israel, This is not the error as it is as per design that Robots takes pause as per the time specified for them. In case of the EUR_EMD5 the pause is for 1 hour so it took the pause for that period after finishing the queue, that’s why the PNR was processed once Robot resumed its processing. Thanks and Regards, Anurag Verma 2/22/2018 7:49:09 PM, NIIT.averma, Since we have not seen this issue before, we have asked Israel for some more examples where we can analyse the pattern. Also there were no errors in the logs seen and robots were also up at that time though there were no processing done by them hence there was no logging in the logs. 2/22/2018 11:43:53 AM, NIIT.averma, I have checked these cases and found that some of the Robots has stopped processing on 14th Feb and resumed their process again on 15th Feb, though there was no error found in the logs and alert or error reported for Robot during that period. The reason for the gap in the processing is not clear as there is no traces. The PNRs provided by you are picked up by these robots on 15th Feb. That’s why the ticket was not processed for a long time when sent to the Robot BATCH. -rw-r--r-- 1 ibrobot ibcomgr 328642 Feb 14 13:41 eur_et1.log.2018-02-14 ibrobot@ibcrobotl:/delivery/robot-batch/ibrobot/logs> vi eur_et1.log.2018-02-15 #16:03:28,699#INFO #eur_et1 - Creando proceso: com.iberia.robot.emision.EmisionETProcess ...

column7: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column13: <ISSUE>:: Errors in application , application was giving intermittent errors.The logs genarted by Ibconecta showed that there were connectivity errors. <IMPACT>:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database and hence no new notifications from IbConecta <ANALYSIS>:: As per the support document incident we request DBA team to check the errors, we check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors but more often than not the connectivity is restored itself. <STEPS TAKEN TO RESOLVE>:: As said, we moitored the database for a while and the connectivity was restored. We checked in the logs to verify the connection. <PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? (Yes, No).>:: NO, because its a pseudo Alarm and we have already worked with Database team to extend the pool size. <CAN THIS INCIDENT BE PREVENTED? (Yes, No)> :: No, Its an intermittent issue, when the database connectivity is lost and Ibconnecta keeps polling for the connection.We had already asked DBA to increase the Pool size.

column13: Issue: Error encountered during execution of IB Card Assignment out File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds data of the Card Assignment points, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Avios points against their Iberia Cards. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully send the IB Card Assignment file to IB Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

column7: LINUX_sun - apliwebl1.ib : Pool JDBC Aeropuertos1^Aeropuertos1^IBCONECTPRO+bdl+ibutf8 no Activo. Avi
column13: Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections as the pool would have depleted. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: "####<ene 30, 2018 3:51:21 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1517323881002> <BEA-310002> <46% of the total memory in the server is free>" Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column13: [26/02/2018] NIIT.mpsingh [issue]: [TRYsTJj50] Gift card consumes the balance without being used [Impact] 1 User [resolution] This is a known issue and should be raised as an enhancement [23/02/2018] NIIT.mpsingh This is a known issue and manual intervention will be required in order to claim the bono if the service has suffered timeout during the consumption. This abnormal behavior of BONO service occurs due to way the application is designed and resolution to this known issue is to implement an enhancement in the application. The same concern has already been conveyed to the business in the past as well. [2018/02/23] LEDA.lnavio: nos infoma IT que en este caso hubo un Timeout del servicio, pero ¿no debería haberse devuelvo el uso al bono? Debido a este timeout, el cliente se quedó con su bono consumido y sin poder usarlo de nuevo. [22/02/2018] NIIT.mpsingh Provided analysis to business as the issue is not in application but seems to be in infrastructure.

[2018/02/26] LEDA.lnavio: reasignamos incidencia planteando la siguiente duda: Con esto que indicas “There are already payment failure alerts in the system that runs on standard cases and based on them we can check whether the problem is at specific server and related to specific type of payment and specific country” à quieres decir que cuando vuelva a ocurrir en el futuro, ¿con estas alertas se podrá detectar el problema en “tiempo real” y no al día siguiente cuando se saquen las gráficas? [2018/02/23]NIIT.vkumar: On the booking flow when customer reaches at prepayment authorization page then system stores the data of some of payment type selected in IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY and its sub parameters. This data relates to user selected options and served withcached xml This is not fixed as the data depends on user opted option and their combinations to populate the value. So parameters can be different based on flow. So it can be or not be null as its populated on run time behavior. It’s not possible to track the old data values from October to December or January based on this periodic dynamic changing the data. So separate alert cannot be set on this. There are already payment failure alerts in the system that runs on standard cases and based on them we can check whether the problem is at specific server and related to specific type of payment and specific country. So while there is this kind of problem so the possibility is to check the flow and look into the parameters that getting the null data and recache them again. E.g. payemtns, As per above form the parameters value depends on form of payments and then its sub elements like card issuing country, type of card OR in case paypel , transfer, installments payments. This behavior is as per existing application design. The stats from 21 to now are almost in equal range.. More detail can be found in attached email. El “problema” como se puede ver en las gráficas adjuntas (gráficas individuales por horas de cada día 18/19/20/21/22FEB) se solventó ese mismo día 19. El día 31JAN parece que lo que fallara fue en la pata A ¿fue el mismo motivo, IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY=null? El 8JAN parece que lo que fallara fue en la pata B ¿fue el mismo motivo, IBP_TARJETA_CREDITO_EXTERNAL_KEY=null? Si analizamos por patas y días las órdenes de compra en .mobi desde el 1NOV, se ve la caída en cada una de las ocasiones descritas ¿es siempre el mismo parámetro el que falla? ¿Por qué falla? Si ya sabemos que falla ¿no se puede poner una alerta? ¿hay algún plan para evitar esto y darnos cuenta siempre al día siguiente? Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: ####<feb 21, 2018 7:31:07 AM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519194667617> <BEA-310002> <49% of the total memory in the server is free> ####<feb 21, 2018 7:35:16 AM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl1.ib> <Aeropuertos1> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519194916455> <BEA-310002> <65% of the total memory in the server is free> Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column7: Escalado Job: LINUX_ibm - El job: X25OBIM2 con OrderID: 30ih9 del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maqu
column13: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso X25OBIM2 porque no ha ejecutado el proceso X25OLST del que controla la condición. Impact: Medio, al no ejecutarse el X25OLST se retrasa la entrega del fichero IB-MERGER-LOADSTATS al proceso que lo explota y por tanto el producto final. Root Cause: El X25OLST no se ejecuto porque el proceso X25OI21 no tenia activiada la condicion FICI281-OK 2002. Steps Taken: Añadir la condicion FICI281-OK 2002 para que se ejecute el proceso X25OI21 y se ejecute el proceso X25OLST. Una vez ejecutado el X25OLST se borra el X25OBIM2 fallado.

column13: Issue : Filthy information seen to be sent as Response emails to the IBPLUS members. Analysis : Since the emails were supposed to be checked at ATOS end, an email was sent to them to look into this & investigate. Steps Taken to Resolve : Since the emails were supposed to be checked at ATOS end, an email was sent to them to look into this & investigate. It seems that one of ATOS testers have used this while testing the email template & had forgotten to remove it. This was corrected at their end. But later on after this was resolved, it was reported that the Response emails to be sent to Silver card holders are using the Clasica template. This also was corrected at ATOS end. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No) : No, this is one of an Instance & handled by the 3rd party & hence no problem ticket required. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)> : No, this is one of an instance and hence, measures cant be taken at our end to avoid this.

column7: LINUX_sun - ERROR en APLICACI?N=IBConecta, CI=HUB003. Avisar Oncall CRM
column13: Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: ####<feb 22, 2018 3:40:11 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519310411525> <BEA-310002> <71% of the total memory in the server is free> Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column13: Issue: Ha fallado el proceso X25OBIM2 porque no ha ejecutado el proceso X25OLST del que controla la condición. Impact: Medio, al no ejecutarse el X25OLST se retrasa la entrega del fichero IB-MERGER-LOADSTATS al proceso que lo explota y por tanto el producto final. Root Cause: El X25OLST no se ejecuto porque no se recibio el fichero ED04.LRESER.A180221. Steps Taken: Una vez recibido el fichero ED04.LRESER.A180221 se ejecuta el proceso D04OCHR. Ejecutandose toda la cadena de procesos hasta la ejecución del proceso X25OLST. Se borra el proceso X25OBIM2 que se encuentra fallado.

ANALISIS DE IMPACTO: Bajo Fallo en la carga de smart ACCIONES REALIZADAS: Se comprueba que ocurre y nos falta el fichero de inventory que se reclama ya que va con bastante retraso, cuando llega se procede a cargarlo de manera manual PRUEBAS REALIZADAS: Se realiza comprobación de que el procesos van correctamente y que las cargas en BBDD han ido correctas

Issue: Error encountered during execution of IB Card Assignment out File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds data of the Card Assignment points, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Avios points against their Iberia Cards. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully send the IB Card Assignment file to IB Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

column7: LINUX_sun - ibclogemltc.ib : Filesystem ib-nfs_backup is occupied 90.06%.
column13: Issue: ELK - NFS backup drive was running on high disk usage Impact: This will impact the backup process of ELK and can result in high disk usage on Data nodes as old indices will not be deleted Analysis: We had a request to restore an old snapshot which lead to high disk usage on backup drive. Resolution: To manage the space in NFS_drive we deleted the snapshot for the current week as indices were still alive. Archived the old snapshot backup-2018.01.22. Also, space on the backup drive is increased from 1TB to 4TB. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, problem ticket is not required as due to a request to restore old snapshot the space on Backup drive was high. This incident can be avoided?: Yes, can be avoided. Now we have allocated more space on the backup drive to avoid such issues in future.

column7: LINUX_sun - nfsla.ib : Filesystem datapro-ib_nfs_backup is occupied 90.08%.
column13: Issue: ELK - High NFS disk space. Analysis: we analyses that on the disk there were more number of snapshots that should not be there. Business impact: If there would be less space in the NFS drive then backup tool will not perform it's activities, thus there would be no snapshot creation, index deletion and archival. there could a huge impact of data mismanagement. Resolution: we removed the latest snapshot and archived the oldest snapshot so that we can have more space on NFS Disk. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as the disk space issue is not raised frequently. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as the NFS backup is includes snapshot and we don't have a fixed size of the snapshots.

Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

Issue: ELK - high swap area occupied on client node ibclogec1.ib Analysis: After running for some time clientnode start to occupy swap area. We have to restart elastcsearch services in order to resolve this. Business impact: High utilization of swap area might result in Clientnode not able to take request responses from Kibana. This can impact users looking at logs from Kibana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch services on client node ibclogec1.ib to resolve this. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as client nodes have light memory leak after running from some time they start occupying swap area. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as it is the functionality of client nodes in ELK they are built on java and have a light memory leak after running from some time.

LINUX_sun - ibcloged1.ib : Filesystem ib-nfs_backup is occupied 90.43%
column13: Issue: ELK - NFS backup drive was running on high disk usage Impact: This will impact the backup process of ELK and can result in high disk usage on Data nodes as old indices will not be deleted Analysis: We had a request to restore an old snapshot which lead to high disk usage on backup drive. Resolution: To manage the space in NFS_drive we deleted the snapshot for the current week as indices were still alive. Archived the old snapshot backup-2018.01.22. Also, space on the backup drive is increased from 1TB to 4TB. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, problem ticket is not required as due to a request to restore old snapshot the space on Backup drive was high. This incident can be avoided?: Yes, can be avoided. Now we have allocated more space on the backup drive to avoid such issues in future.

column7: LINUX_sun - nfsla.ib : Filesystem datapro-ib_nfs_backup is occupied 90.26%.
column13: Issue: ELK - High NFS disk space. Analysis: we analyses that on the disk there were more number of snapshots that should not be there. Business impact: If there would be less space in the NFS drive then backup tool will not perform it's activities, thus there would be no snapshot creation, index deletion and archival. there could a huge impact of data mismanagement. Resolution: we removed the latest snapshot and archived the oldest snapshot so that we can have more space on NFS Disk. Problem Ticket required(Y/N): No, as the disk space issue is not raised frequently. Can this incident be prevented?; No, as the NFS backup is includes snapshot and we don't have a fixed size of the snapshots.

Issue:: we are getting "Reached maximum capacity of pool" in IBCONECTA logs. Impact:: If error messages will not resolve on time , the application would have not been able to create new connections with the Database. Analysis:: We check the blocking session on DB, we also checked in concerned logs for the specified errors, There are no errors now. There is sufficient memory. Latest logs are as below: ####<feb 26, 2018 12:47:57 PM CET> <Info> <Health> <apliwebl2.ib> <Aeropuertos2> <weblogic.GCMonitor> <<anonymous>> <> <> <1519645677184> <BEA-310002> <50% of the total memory in the server is free> Steps Taken to Resolve:: We have monitor the IBCONECTA logs after sometime we found that the memory gets free automatically. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).:: No, because this is a pseudo alarm and this is handled internally by the system, we need this as it monitors the error in advance and sends us alarm as incidents. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No) :: No, This is an alarm which is raised by the system and is handled internally, but we need to look if the handler is not done, which is not the case here.

column13: Issue: ELK - User was not able to see logs in Kibana Analysis: During the initial analysis of the issue, the dashboard which user was looking for in KIbana was working for us and all the nodes in ELK platform were up and running. However, later the requests to Kibana were not going through and in logs we checked that the OutOfMemoryerror were found on client nodes. Impact: Requests through Kibana were not getting responded to and hence it impacted the logs or reports users were looking at in KIbana. Resolution: We restarted elasticsearch on client nodes and started going through the flow. Problem Ticket required: No, as client nodes were overloaded which caused the outofmemory error and resolved after restarting the client nodes. HOwever, as the user base of the ELK platform is increasing and hence the load on the lcuster, we will need to increase the RAM on CLient nodes. Is this incident can be avoided: No, as the client nodes were experiencing high volume of request this incident cannot be avoided. We can increase the RAM on the client nodes as the user base of ELK platform is increasing.

column13: Issue: Error encountered during execution of Partial Reversal File. Business Impact: Delay in file execution is critical to Iberia cards since it holds data of the active customers in Spain based on which business rules are created to calculate the accrued points, programs etc. Analysis: File arrived late hence the load plan failed.Therefore manually re ran the load plan to successfully load the partial reversal file. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for IB Card Assignment file to successfully process the load. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED? : No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.
